1 qt bottle drank with dinner at Moab Brewery. Well balanced malts, chocolate and coffee notes prominent . Very drinkable!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Moab Brewery Desert Select Export Stout

review_blob:
Aged for one year in beer fridge. Accompanied by pumpkin pie. Alcohol and malts prevalent, along with some tropical fruit esters. Pumpkin subdued, and so were pie spice notes. Interesting to compare fresh and aged version. This was a drinkable yet subdued brew.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
